Dialogue.Value: It’s a guide to using good,manners on the Internet.
It used to be called,”netiquette”，but nobody,uses that word anymore.
It’s a brief history of how,computers were invented.
Writing the history of,computers on paper is,kinda ironic.
Alright，everyone turn on your,computers and jack in.
For today’s class，you’ll be,fighting real viruses.
I already explained it last,week，but I’ll explain it again,just to be safe.
Virus busting is using your,Navi to delete viruses on a,computer.
Originally，viruses were simply,bad programs which made,computers malfunction.
In the cyberworld，they can,look like animals and batteries，,and they’ll attack Navis.
Early Navis had no combat,capabilities，so they were,defenseless against viruses.
However，new technology,allowed us to equip our Navis,with weapons.
We made Battle Chips，,and now our Navis can,fight off viruses.
I’ll let my Navi explain the,details.
Equipping a Navi with,weapons is not easy.,In fact，it is quite difficult.
Weapons were orginially built,into the Navi，making already,large Navis even larger.
From this，high-capacity and,low cost ”Chip Cards” were,invented.
Weapon data is stored on,the Chip Card and then sent,to the Navi.
This is how and why we use,Battle Chips.
I have yet to explain the,Chip Folder and Chip Slot-In,Tool，but....
for convenience，I’ll cover,those topics after the exam.
Did you remember all that,from last week?
Now，we’ll test how well you,can fight against viruses.
Is there anyone who would like,me to explain how to operate?
If you want help，just raise,your hand.
Ms. Asakura! Over here!
Me too! We should probably,pay attention.
Do you remember what to do，,Shanghai?
Uh....,I can’t remember....
Ms. Asakura，I think my,Navi doesn’t understand.
Could you help us?
Alright，I’ll go around and,help the students who raised,their hands.
I’ll hold your hand through the,first four fights.
But you’ll be graded on the,fifth fight，so be sure to pay,attention!
Be careful not to make a,mistake and get your Navi,deleted!
Okay! Here we go!
Battle Routine! Set!
Well done，everyone!
That’s all for today’s lesson!
We covered important,material，so write it down,before you forget.
Today’s and last week’s,material will be on the,final exam.
Class is dismissed.,Have a good day.
Thank you，teacher!
Thank you!
Ah，you came.,Let’s get started.
First，give me your PET so I,can transfer its data to the PC.
Here you go，Ms. Asakura.
A high-capacity Navi，huh....?
It’s weird.,Shanghai is larger than most,other Navis combined.
Don’t talk about fat people,right in front of them! It’s rude!
Fufu....,Clearly she’s a special Navi.
Initializing the Scan Program....,Scanning data....
#b@false#.......#b@true#There. Done.
Here’s your PET.
It doesn’t look like there are,any anomalies. That’s a relief.
Hold on. Is that a,compressed data file?
Oh，that! Someone buried it in,Genso Area. It looks like some,kind of treasure data.
Unfortunately，we can’t figure,out how to decompress it.
Some strange thugs were,looking for it，so it’s probably,valuable.
I see. Maybe you should,see Dr. Morichika.
Morichika....?,Where have I heard that,name before....?
Mari!,It’s Mari’s last name!
Ah，that girl might be his,daughter.
Dr. Morichika is a professor,at Genso University. He laid,the groundwork for today’s
Internet.,I wonder if he can also analyze,your data for you.
A professor?,What’s that?
Basically，it’s someone who,teaches classes at a university.
You’re only in middle school，,so it makes sense that you,wouldn’t know.
Then why do I feel like an,idiot....?
Well，maybe Dr. Morichika,can help with our data if we,pay him a visit.
We can go right now if you,want.
Would it bother him if we,went right now?
Let’s just leave that to Mari.,She’ll come up with something.
....Then let’s try asking her,first.
Thank you，Ms. Asakura!
If anything is bothering you，,don’t be afraid to ask for help.
You are representing your,school，so please be on your,best behavior.
Ah，Alice!,Do you need something?
Kumami asked me if you,could return her Navi.
My sister?
Well....,I’d love to，but now’s not the,best time.
Weren’t you just reorganizing,the database?
That’s just it.,It looks like some viruses,got into the book data.
Those viruses shouldn’t be,that big of a deal，right?
True，but my sister’s Navi,can’t actually fight.
(A Navi light enough to, send by email....)
I was thinking about calling,someone for help.
Those little....!,Alice! Jack me in!
I’ll tidy up those viruses,nice ’n quick!
Y-Yeah! Got it!
Thank you，Alice!,You really helped me out!
Don’t mention it! We were just,doing Kumami a favor.
And with that，all our errands,are done! Man，I’m beat!
That was a lot of stuff to do,in one day....
Oh yeah，have you seen,Remilia?
Ms. Scarlet?,Why? Is she alright?
Ah，never mind!,It’s nothing!
She’s the youngest in the,class，so she might be feeling,lonely....
That brat? Lonely?
Even though she skipped a,few grades，she’s still a child.,Treat her gently.
Now that Patchouli’s gone，,I have to get a new Navi.
Do you have one in mind?
I’ll talk it over with my sister,and take some time to decide.
It’s a fancy teacher’s desk.
The most high-tech computer,in the school is in this desk.
It was designed so that it can’t,be used without a teacher’s ID.
It’s a fancy teacher’s desk.
The most high-tech computer,in the school is in this desk.
It’s currently connected to the,library’s server.,I can access it by jacking in.
It’s a high-tech desk with a,computer built-in.
They call it high-tech，but,the tech inside is actually,pretty old.
Students can only jack in,during class.
